hello, I am trying to update my web3 dependencies, from 1.7.0 to 4.2.0 and get the following error:
```
 TransactionRevertInstructionError: Transaction has been reverted by the EVM
    at /home/test/node_modules/web3-eth/lib/commonjs/utils/get_transaction_error.js:48:21
    at Generator.next (<anonymous>)
    at /home/test/node_modules/web3-eth/lib/commonjs/utils/get_transaction_error.js:24:71
    at new Promise (<anonymous>)
    at __awaiter (/home/test/node_modules/web3-eth/lib/commonjs/utils/get_transaction_error.js:20:12)
    at getTransactionError (/home/test/node_modules/web3-eth/lib/commonjs/utils/get_transaction_error.js:33:12)
    at SendTxHelper.<anonymous> (/home/test/node_modules/web3-eth/lib/commonjs/utils/send_tx_helper.js:74:84)
    at Generator.next (<anonymous>)
    at fulfilled (/home/test/node_modules/web3-eth/lib/commonjs/utils/send_tx_helper.js:5:58)
    at process.processTicksAndRejections (node:internal/process/task_queues:95:5) {
  innerError: undefined,
  reason: 'err: insufficient funds for gas * price + value: address 0x4b3ABe20fb75a3D0B3c9dF385Ebf3721dA284eb1 have 51039247781579884 want 725244160242779704823955000000 (supplied gas 3000000)',
  signature: undefined,
  receipt: undefined,
  data: undefined,
  code: 402
}
```
it is requiring a far more reasonable gas of `725244160242779704823955000000`, the exact same transaction can be sent via 1.7.0 without error. The transaction looks like this
```
async function test() {
    let accountNonce = await web3.eth.getTransactionCount(recipient, 'pending');
    accountNonce = Number(accountNonce)
    const rawBuyTx = {
        nonce: accountNonce,
        gasPrice: '0xb2d05e00',
        gasLimit: '0x2dc6c0',
        to: '0x49fa1603fc4e795f111b044e5283832779fa9ecd',
        value: '0x0',
        data: '...'
    }
    const buyTx = LegacyTransaction.fromTxData(rawBuyTx, { common: customCommon })
    const signedTx = buyTx.sign(hexToBytes(privatekey));
    accountNonce = accountNonce + 1;
    try {
        const result = await web3.eth.sendSignedTransaction(signedTx.serialize());

    } catch (error) {
        console.log(error)
    }
}

test()
```
A bit similar with #6249 , but I think I am facing a different situation. I am sending this transactoin on bsc mainnet. I try to put extra gas in the wallet but still get the error. And the 725244160242779704823955000000 keep the same whenever this error occurs. Can someone help me to locate the problem?

